<h1> Solution Art Gallery </h1>

<br></br>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
    <h2>Overview:</h2>
     <p>The Solution Art Gallery play helps teams get specific on what they believe is the 'solution' within the value proposition. Teams typically use this play as a follow on to Crazy 8's, taking their best ideas and flushing them out with art gallery detail. An art gallery for a solution is more than just a sketch, its the articulation of what specific problem & for who it is being solved, with what solution, and what expected result/value. This three part approach is given a descriptive yet catchy title so that when its presented back to the team, sticky dot voting can be done by the team to identify what resonates with the team the most. There are many variations to this play - from what the three parts are to what type of voting is conducted.</p>
      </div>
  </div>

